4:
Gaze upon these brushstrokes,
which are surpassed in beauty only
by the artist! You could take this
scroll home with you today for the
low price of...
7:
Take a look at this frame! Collectors
will appreciate the fine mahogany
and...
13:
Is there no form of culture that
merchants will not convert into gold?
16:
I mean, people DO have to make a
living...
20:
You know what they say. The best
things in life... present ripe business
opportunities...
24:
I do not think a price should be laid
upon tradition and beauty...
27:
Well, at least we can say our plan
was a success. Kakizome has
definitely caught on in Palpebra.
30:
Yeah. And it's not a bad thing that
people appreciate calligraphy
enough to buy it, right?
34:
No, it isn't. But when culture is turned
into commodity, some lose sight of
its original meaning. Then it
becomes merely a circus act to be
profited off of.
37: Oh. Heh. Funny you should say that.
39:
So... there's actually this show
coming up...
42:
Ladies and gentlemen, boys and
girls! Perk up your ears and open
your eyes!
43:
May I present to you the wonderful
world of words as you've never seen
it before!
45:
Stretched before me is a
snow-white canvas, spanning the
width of a whole street. Onto this
canvas, a single, elegant character
is about to be written.
46:
And here to perform the feat,
wielding a brush almost a tall as
herself, is the sensational mind
behind the first kakizome
competition... Luluca from the
Oculus!
52:
Everyone likes a good show. If it's big
and it's flashy, it's headed for
success.
58:
Ohh... I'm getting nervous. What if I
mess up?
65: How can you be so sure?
69:
You practiced endlessly for this day.
Have some faith in yourself.
73:
Yeah... You're right! Phew, okay! I got
this!
94:
Hehe. Guess all that hard work paid
off.
95:
I love just sitting down with a brush
and DOING calligraphy, but that's
not all...
97:
I love communicating with people.
Both through my articles and my art.
98:
And this time, what I wanted to say
was...
101: "Make this year a year to celebrate!"
104:
What is written on this one? It seems
to be in the ancient speech of the
Farlands.
106:
Ah... You are gazing at words of love,
my friend, offered by a great knight
to the lady of his heart. They come
from an old epic, which was written
down by a famous poet.
108:
Direct your attention to the rough,
passionate strokes. One can FEEL the
knight's burning love emanating
from the canvas!
109:
Hm... If you're looking for a buyer, I
know someone who'd pay good
money for such a masterpiece.
110:
Do you now?! Well, let's set up a time
and meeting place...
113:
Perhaps it is the fate of all art to be
admired in an auction house...
117:
You know, you COULD say
kakizome's been assimilated into
Palpebran culture.
125:
We're a city of businesspeople!
Well, I'm off to conduct interviews for
our super-duper calligraphy edition.
Don't miss it when it hits the stands!
